151            $expected_url = [ 'pb_cover_image' ];
152            foreach ( get_post_meta( $meta_post->ID ) as $key => $val ) {
153                // Skip anything not prefixed with pb_
154                if ( 0 !== strpos( $key, 'pb_' ) ) {

157                // Skip contributor meta (already done, look up)

167
168                // We only care about strings
169                if ( is_array( $val ) ) {

171                        $val = implode( ', ', $val );
172                    } else {

175                    }
176                }

182
183                if ( false !== in_array( $key, $expected_the_content, true ) ) {

185                    $val = wpautop( $val );
186                } else {
187                    $val = htmlspecialchars( $val, ENT_NOQUOTES | ENT_XHTML, 'UTF-8', false );
188                }
189
190                // Normalize URLs
191                if ( in_array( $key, $expected_url, true ) ) {

193                }
194
195                // Remove invisible control characters that break XML
196                $val = \Pressbooks\Sanitize\remove_control_characters( $val );
197
198                $book_information[ $key ] = $val;
199            }
200        }
201
202        // Return our best guess if no book information has been entered.
203        if ( empty( $book_information ) ) {
204            $book_information['pb_title'] = get_bloginfo( 'name' );
205            if ( ! function_exists( 'get_user_by' ) ) {

209            $author_metadata = $author->display_name ?? '';
210            $book_information['pb_authors'] = $contributors_as_string ? $author_metadata : [ [ 'name' => $author_metadata ] ];

212        }

215        // Cache & Return
216        // -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
217

222        if ( ! empty( $id ) && is_int( $id ) ) {

224        }
225
226        return $book_information;
227    }

400                'post_parent' => $post->post_parent,
401                'export' => ( isset( $post_ids_to_export[ $post->ID ] ) && 'on' === $post_ids_to_export[ $post->ID ] ) ? true : false,
402                'has_post_content' => ! empty( trim( $post->post_content ) ),
403                'word_count' => \Pressbooks\Utility\word_count( $post->post_content ),
404            ];
405        }
406
407        // -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
408        // Add Chapters to Parts
409        // -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
410
411        foreach ( $book_structure['part'] as $i => $part ) {
412            // There's no `pb_export` for parts. We instead have `pb_part_invisible` and it doesn't mean the same thing. Force to true.
413            $book_structure['part'][ $i ]['export'] = true;
414            $book_structure['part'][ $i ]['chapters'] = [];
415        }
416
417        foreach ( $book_structure['chapter'] as $i => $chapter ) {
418            foreach ( $book_structure['part'] as $j => $part ) {
419                if ( $part['ID'] === $chapter['post_parent'] ) {
420                    $book_structure['part'][ $j ]['chapters'][] = $chapter;
421                    unset( $book_structure['chapter'][ $i ] );
422                    continue 2;
423                }
424            }
425        }
426
427        /* Track unexpected orphans, unset() chapter from $book_structure and $types */
428
429        if ( count( $book_structure['chapter'] ) ) {
430            $book_structure['__orphans'] = $book_structure['chapter'];
431        }
432
433        unset( $book_structure['chapter'] );
434        $custom_types = array_diff( $custom_types, [ 'chapter' ] );
435
436        // -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
437        // Create __order arrays, remove post_parent
438        // -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
439
440        $book_structure['__order'] = [];
441        foreach ( $custom_types as $type ) {
442            foreach ( $book_structure[ $type ] as $i => $struct ) {
443                unset( $book_structure[ $type ][ $i ]['post_parent'] );
444                if ( 'part' !== $type ) {
445                    $book_structure['__order'][ $struct['ID'] ] = [
446                        'export' => $struct['export'],
447                        'post_status' => $struct['post_status'],
448                        'post_name' => $struct['post_name'],
449                        'post_type' => $type,
450                    ];
451                } else {
452                    if ( $struct['has_post_content'] && get_post_meta( $struct['ID'], 'pb_part_invisible', true ) !== 'on' ) {
453                        $book_structure['__order'][ $struct['ID'] ] = [
454                            'export' => $struct['export'],
455                            'post_status' => $struct['post_status'],
456                            'post_name' => $struct['post_name'],
457                            'post_type' => 'part',
458                        ];
459                    }
460                    foreach ( $struct['chapters'] as $j => $chapter ) {
461                        unset( $book_structure[ $type ][ $i ]['chapters'][ $j ]['post_parent'] );
462                        if ( $struct['has_post_content'] && get_post_meta( $struct['ID'], 'pb_part_invisible', true ) !== 'on' ) {
463                            $book_structure['__order'][ $struct['ID'] ] = [
464                                'export' => $struct['export'],
465                                'post_status' => $struct['post_status'],
466                                'post_name' => $struct['post_name'],
467                                'post_type' => 'part',
468                            ];
469                        }
470                        $book_structure['__order'][ $chapter['ID'] ] = [
471                            'export' => $chapter['export'],
472                            'post_status' => $chapter['post_status'],
473                            'post_name' => $chapter['post_name'],
474                            'post_type' => 'chapter',
475                        ];
476                    }
477                }
478            }
479        }
480        static::$__order = $book_structure['__order'];
481
482        // -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
483        // Cache & Return
484        // -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
485
486        if ( static::useCache() ) {
487            wp_cache_set( $cache_id, $book_structure, 'pb', DAY_IN_SECONDS );
488        }
489
490        if ( ! empty( $id ) && is_int( $id ) ) {
491            restore_current_blog();
492        }
493
494        return $book_structure;
495    }
496
497    /**
498     * Returns an array representing the entire structure of a book, in correct order,
499     * with a maximum amount of fields. Data is raw and must be post-processed.
500     *
501     * @see bottom of this file for more info
502     * @return array
503     */
504    static function getBookContents() {
505
506        global $blog_id;
507
508        // -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
509        // Is cached?
510        // -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
511
512        $cache_id = "book-cnt-$blog_id";
513        if ( static::useCache() ) {
514            $book_contents = wp_cache_get( $cache_id, 'pb' );
515            if ( $book_contents ) {
516                return $book_contents;
517            }
518        }
519
520        // -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
521        // Using + to merge arrays...
522        // Precedence when using the + operator to merge arrays is from left to right
523        // -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
524
525        $book_contents = static::getBookStructure();
526
527        foreach ( $book_contents as $type => $struct ) {
528
529            if ( preg_match( '/^__/', $type ) ) {
530                continue; // Skip __magic keys
531            }
532
533            if ( 'part' === $type ) {
534                foreach ( $struct as $i => $part ) {
535                    $book_contents[ $type ][ $i ] = $part + get_post( $part['ID'], ARRAY_A );
536                    foreach ( $part['chapters'] as $j => $chapter ) {
537                        $book_contents[ $type ][ $i ]['chapters'][ $j ] = $chapter + get_post( $chapter['ID'], ARRAY_A );
538                    }
539                }
540            } else {
541                foreach ( $struct as $i => $val ) {
542                    $book_contents[ $type ][ $i ] = $val + get_post( $val['ID'], ARRAY_A );
543                }
544            }
545        }
546
547        // -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
548        // Cache & Return
549        // -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
550
551        if ( static::useCache() ) {
552            wp_cache_set( $cache_id, $book_contents, 'pb', DAY_IN_SECONDS );
553        }
554
555        return $book_contents;
556    }

558    /**
559     * @param bool $selected_for_export (optional)
560     *
561     * @return int
562     */
563    static function wordCount( $selected_for_export = false ) {
564        $wc = 0;
565        $wc_selected_for_export = 0;
566        foreach ( static::getBookStructure() as $key => $section ) {
567            if ( $key === 'front-matter' || $key === 'back-matter' ) {
568                foreach ( $section as $val ) {
569                    $wc += $val['word_count'];
570                    if ( $val['export'] ) {
571                        $wc_selected_for_export += $val['word_count'];
572                    }
573                }
574            }
575            if ( $key === 'part' ) {
576                foreach ( $section as $part ) {
577                    foreach ( $part['chapters'] as $val ) {
578                        $wc += $val['word_count'];
579                        if ( $val['export'] ) {
580                            $wc_selected_for_export += $val['word_count'];
581                        }
582                    }
583                }
584            }
585        }
586
587        return $selected_for_export ? $wc_selected_for_export : $wc;
588    }

611        static::$__order = [];

631    /**
632     * Returns an array of subsections in front matter, back matter, or chapters.
633     *
634     * @param $id
635     *
636     * @return array|false
637     */
638    static function getSubsections( $id ) {
639        $parent = get_post( $id );
640        if ( empty( $parent ) ) {
641            return false;
642        }
643        $has_heading_shortcode = has_shortcode( $parent->post_content, 'heading' );
644        if ( stripos( $parent->post_content, '<h1' ) === false && $has_heading_shortcode === false ) {
645            // No <h1> or [heading] shortcode, nothing to do
646            return false;
647        }
648
649        if ( $has_heading_shortcode ) {
650            // Only render heading shortcode into <h1> if we have to
651            $content = \Pressbooks\Utility\do_shortcode_by_tags( $parent->post_content, [ 'heading' ] );
652            $content = strip_shortcodes( $content );
653        } else {
654            $content = $parent->post_content;
655        }
656        $content = strip_tags( $content, '<h1>' );  // Strip everything except <h1> to speed up load time
657
658        $type = $parent->post_type;
659        $output = [];
660        $s = 1;
661
662        $doc = new HtmlParser( true ); // Because we are not saving, use internal parser to speed up load time
663        $dom = $doc->loadHTML( $content );
664        $sections = $dom->getElementsByTagName( 'h1' );
665        foreach ( $sections as $section ) {
666            /** @var $section \DOMElement */
667            $output[ $type . '-' . $id . '-section-' . $s ] = wptexturize( $section->textContent );
668            $s++;
669        }
670
671        if ( empty( $output ) ) {
672            return false;
673        }
674
675        return $output;
676    }
677
678    /**
679     * Returns an array of front matter, chapters, and back matter which contain subsections.
680     *
681     * @param array $book_structure The book structure from getBookStructure()
682     * @return array The subsections, grouped by parent post type
683     */
684    static function getAllSubsections( $book_structure ) {
685        if ( Export::shouldParseSubsections() ) {
686            $book_subsections_transient = \Pressbooks\Book::SUBSECTIONS_TRANSIENT;
687            $subsection_processing_transient = \Pressbooks\Book::SUBSECTION_PROCESSING_TRANSIENT;
688            $book_subsections = get_transient( $book_subsections_transient );
689            if ( ! $book_subsections ) {
690                $book_subsections = [];
691                if ( ! get_transient( $subsection_processing_transient ) ) {
692                    set_transient( $subsection_processing_transient, 1, 5 * MINUTE_IN_SECONDS );
693                    foreach ( $book_structure['front-matter'] as $section ) {
694                        $subsections = \Pressbooks\Book::getSubsections( $section['ID'] );
695                        if ( $subsections ) {
696                            $book_subsections['front-matter'][ $section['ID'] ] = $subsections;
697                        }
698                    }
699                    foreach ( $book_structure['part'] as $key => $part ) {
700                        if ( ! empty( $part['chapters'] ) ) {
701                            foreach ( $part['chapters'] as $section ) {
702                                $subsections = \Pressbooks\Book::getSubsections( $section['ID'] );
703                                if ( $subsections ) {
704                                    $book_subsections['chapters'][ $section['ID'] ] = $subsections;
705                                }
706                            }
707                        }
708                    }
709                    foreach ( $book_structure['back-matter'] as $section ) {
710                        $subsections = \Pressbooks\Book::getSubsections( $section['ID'] );
711                        if ( $subsections ) {
712                            $book_subsections['back-matter'][ $section['ID'] ] = $subsections;
713                        }
714                    }
715                    delete_transient( $subsection_processing_transient );
716                }
717            }
718            set_transient( $book_subsections_transient, $book_subsections );
719            return $book_subsections;
720        }
721        return [];
722    }
723
724    /**
725     * Returns chapter, front or back matter content with section ID and classes added.
726     *
727     * @param string $content
728     * @param int $id
729     *
730     * @return string|false
731     */
732    static function tagSubsections( $content, $id ) {
733        $parent = get_post( $id );
734        if ( empty( $parent ) ) {
735            return false;
736        }
737        if ( stripos( $content, '<h1' ) === false ) {
738            return false;
739        }
740
741        $type = $parent->post_type;
742        $s = 1;
743
744        $doc = new HtmlParser();
745        $dom = $doc->loadHTML( $content );
746        $sections = $dom->getElementsByTagName( 'h1' );
747        foreach ( $sections as $section ) {
748            /** @var $section \DOMElement */
749            $old_id = $section->getAttribute( 'id' );
750            $old_class = $section->getAttribute( 'class' );
751            $new_id = "{$type}-{$id}-section-" . $s++;
752            $new_class = trim( "section-header {$old_class} {$old_id}" );
753            $section->setAttribute( 'id', $new_id );
754            $section->setAttribute( 'class', $new_class );
755        }
756
757        return $doc->saveHTML( $dom );
758    }

760    /**
761     * WP_Ajax hook. Updates a post's privacy setting (whether the post is published or privately published)
762     */
763    static function updateGlobalPrivacyOptions() {
764        if ( check_ajax_referer( 'pb-organize-book-privacy' ) ) {
765            $blog_public = absint( $_POST['blog_public'] );
766
767            if ( current_user_can( 'manage_options' ) ) {
768                update_option( 'blog_public', $blog_public );
769            }
770        }
771    }
772
773    /**
774     * Fetch next, previous or first post
775     *
776     * @param string $what prev, next or first
777     * @param bool $return_post_id (optional)
778     * @param bool $admin_mode (optional)
779     *
780     * @return mixed URL of requested post, or Post ID if $return_post_id is set to true
781     */
782    static function get( $what = 'next', $return_post_id = false, $admin_mode = false ) {
783
784        if ( 'first' === $what ) {
785            return static::getFirst( $return_post_id, $admin_mode );
786        }
787
788        global $blog_id;
789
790        global $post;
791
792        $current_post_id = $post->ID;
793        $book_structure = static::getBookStructure();
794        $order = $book_structure['__order'];
795        $pos = array_keys( $order );
796
797        $what = ( 'next' === $what ? 'next' : 'prev' );
798
799        // Move internal pointer to correct position
800        reset( $pos );
801        while ( $find_me = current( $pos ) ) { // @phpcs:ignore
802            if ( (int) $find_me === (int) $current_post_id ) {
803                break;
804            } else {
805                next( $pos );
806            }
807        }
808
809        // Get next/previous
810        $what( $pos );
811        while ( $post_id = current( $pos ) ) { // @phpcs:ignore
812            if ( $admin_mode ) {
813                if ( current_user_can( 'edit_post', $post_id ) ) {
814                    break;
815                } else {
816                    $what( $pos );
817                }
818            } else {
819                if ( in_array( $order[ $post_id ]['post_status'], [ 'publish', 'web-only' ], true ) ) {
820                    break;
821                } elseif ( current_user_can_for_blog( $blog_id, 'read_private_posts' ) ) {
822                    break;
823                } elseif ( get_option( 'permissive_private_content' ) && current_user_can_for_blog( $blog_id, 'read' ) ) {
824                    break;
825                } else {
826                    $what( $pos );
827                }
828            }
829        }
830
831        if ( $return_post_id ) {
832            return (int) $post_id;
833        } else {
834            return ( empty( $post_id ) ) ? '/' : get_permalink( $post_id );
835        }
836    }
837
838    /**
839     * Select the very first post in a book. May be a chapter or a front matter post
840     *
841     * @param bool $return_post_id (optional)
842     * @param bool $admin_mode (optional)
843     *
844     * @return mixed URL of first post, or Post ID if $return_post_id is set to true
845     */
846    static function getFirst( $return_post_id = false, $admin_mode = false ) {
847
848        global $blog_id;
849
850        $book_structure = static::getBookStructure();
851        $order = $book_structure['__order'];
852        $pos = array_keys( $order );
853
854        reset( $pos );
855        while ( $first_id = current( $pos ) ) { // @phpcs:disable WordPress.CodeAnalysis.AssignmentInCondition.FoundInWhileCondition
856            if ( $admin_mode ) {
857                if ( current_user_can( 'edit_post', $first_id ) ) {
858                    break;
859                } else {
860                    next( $pos );
861                }
862            } else {
863                if ( in_array( $order[ $first_id ]['post_status'], [ 'publish', 'web-only' ], true ) ) {
864                    break;
865                } elseif ( current_user_can_for_blog( $blog_id, 'read_private_posts' ) ) {
866                    break;
867                } elseif ( get_option( 'permissive_private_content' ) && current_user_can_for_blog( $blog_id, 'read' ) ) {
868                    break;
869                } else {
870                    next( $pos );
871                }
872            }
873        }
874
875        if ( $return_post_id ) {
876            return (int) $first_id;
877        } else {
